<Placemark><name>🇻🇪 Venezuela — US Intervention / Remote Coercion ◆</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Venezuela — US Intervention / Remote Coercion</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> South America | <b>Index:</b> 71/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Status:</b> VOLATILE<br/><b>Human cost:</b> Op Absolute Resolve (Jan 3): Maduro security team largely killed; 32 Cuban soldiers killed; 7 US wounded<br/><b>Note:</b> NEW THEATER (backfilled) · Jan 3 2026: Operation Absolute Resolve — US strikes on Caracas, Maduro + Cilia Flores captured, flown to NY on USS IWO JIMA (2h28m op) · VP Delcy Rodríguez sworn interim · Trump: 'We\'re going to run the country' · naval armada + tanker blockade remain · $2B stranded-crude export deal; first $500M sale ($300M to Caracas) · May: Alex Saab deported · Jun: Tren de Aragua chief Niño Guerrero killed in JOINT US-Venezuela op · Jun: earthquakes; Mexico aid via Rodríguez call · USER WARGAME LAYER: 44-asset pre-war order of battle (Ford CSG, Iwo Jima ARG, El Libertador Iran-UAV hub, S-300 IADS, Amuay/El Palito) staged into master KML · UPDATE (Jul): oil exports at 7-YEAR HIGH (~1M+ bpd, ~1% of global demand); CFR est. ~$8B exported Jan-Apr (a FLOOR — Trump admin shares no data, proceeds routed through Qatar account, transparency questioned by Congress); most goes to US Gulf refineries, then India · Cabello (Interior Min, $25M US bounty) given ultimatum: cooperate w/ transition or face arrest; Padrino ($15M bounty) holds military chain · Rodríguez wants $5B IMF Special Drawing Rights (blocked since 2019) — her key unmet ask; Rubio: Venezuela submits MONTHLY budget requests for State Dept approval · 621 of ~800 political prisoners released; ~400+ still held<br/><b>Gov:</b> US Congress (CRS): Administration notified Congress of 'non-international armed conflict' with cartels in Venezuela and beyond; War Powers resolutions (S.J.Res.83/90) considered, not passed | US Treasury TIC / DOJ: Maduro + Flores arraigned SDNY on narco-terrorism; $50M bounty claimed by US itself | China MFA / EU (Kallas): China demands Maduro's immediate release ('blatant use of force against a sovereign state'); EU-minus-Hungary calls for restraint under UN Charter | UK House of Commons Library: Cuba confirmed 32 soldiers killed; large part of Maduro's security team killed; legality questioned under international law<br/><b>Econ leverage:</b> China (Export market) [HIGH] | United States (Finance / legal / blockade) [HIGH] | Russia + Iran (Diluents / inputs) [HIGH]<br/><b>◆ External actors:</b> 🇮🇷 Iran→pre-capture regime [DOCUMENTED]: El Libertador UAV hub (Mohajer line — SAME drones as Sahel/Sudan); CAVIM assembly; advisors | 🇨🇳 China→regime [DOCUMENTED]: 80-84% oil-export market; $10B debt; credit-for-oil | 🇷🇺 Russia→regime [DOCUMENTED]: Roszarubezhneft JV; naphtha diluent; advisory footprint (degraded post-capture)<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Venezuela enters at 71 with a backfilled arc — high but stable, because the kinetic phase ended in January and what remains is an occupation-by-leverage in uneasy equilibrium. The user's pre-war wargame layer proved predictive (it mapped the Iwo Jima ARG that carried Maduro out) and now anchors the theater's geography. The unresolved contradictions set the trajectory: China holds the export market the US plan needs; the generals hold the streets the transition needs; and the coercive model that secured control may be incompatible with the investment climate required to monetize it. JULY UPDATE<br/><i>v17.0 · Week 13 verify</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-66.9,10.48,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🇨🇴 Colombia — Rightward Rupture + US Collision</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Colombia — Rightward Rupture + US Collision</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> South America | <b>Index:</b> 67/100 (Δ +1)<br/><b>Status:</b> VOLATILE<br/><b>Human cost:</b> Election-night clashes in Cali; armed-group coercion reported in rural areas<br/><b>Note:</b> NEW THEATER (backfilled) · MAY 31 first round: Espriella 43.7% / Cepeda 40.9% · JUN 21 runoff: Espriella 49.66% vs 48.70% (~250k votes; 63.6% turnout; 12.9M votes = most in Colombian history) · certified Jun 24; Cepeda conceded; Petro alleged fraud/foreign interference but recognized results · INAUGURATION AUG 7 · pledges: 90-day military offensive, 10 Bukele-style mega-prisons, fracking, end peace talks, Israel ties + Jerusalem embassy · pre-arc: DEA named Petro \'priority target\', US sanctioned him · DISPUTED: worker-coercion complaints (59 companies), armed-group pressure, AtlasIntel poll suspension · inauguration AUG 7 approaching; transition tensions rising · UPDATE (Jul): US flagged Colombia not yet cooperative enough to join 'Shield of the Americas'; Petro (outgoing) skipped Doral summit with Lula+Sheinbaum · Espriella already declaring Mexican cartels military targets in Colombian territory pre-inauguration — drew Sheinbaum rebuke · CELAC-Africa summit was hosted in Bogotá (Petro's Global-South alignment) — sharp contrast to incoming Espriella's US-alignment<br/><b>Gov:</b> Registraduría / CNE: Certified Jun 24: 49.66% vs 48.70%; 63.6% turnout; AtlasIntel polls suspended May 19 over methodology (probe ongoing) | US State (Rubio) / Trump: Endorsement + 'Colombia's best days are ahead'; earlier sanctioned Petro; DEA priority-target designation | Colombia Ombudsman / Min. of Labor: Pre-election warnings on armed-group coercion; complaints from workers of 59 companies alleging vote coercion<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Colombia enters at 66, trend up toward the August 7 inauguration — the next hard calendar item after Iran's July cliffs and Sudan's July 7. The theater's core tension: a mandate for maximum force delivered by a minimum margin, against armed groups with proven capacity to answer offensives, under a US administration that has already shown (Venezuela) what the Donroe Doctrine permits. The 90-day offensive's first weeks will set the escalation curve. JULY UPDATE: the handover is the story — outgoing Petro hosted a CELAC-Africa summit in Bogotá (Global-South alignment) and skipped Trump's Doral su<br/><i>v17.0 · Week 13 verify</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-political</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-74.1,4.7,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
